<font class="pn-normal">Your waffle graf (among other things) is dead on. I find that after years of writing and being edited, I finally remember to go back and hack the first 1, 2, 3...sometimes several grafs off the top. Almost always, I waste those words in developing the article in just setting tone or defining the space the article covers.<br />
<br />
Now, I've managed to typically either write a good lead graf, or I chop down to the real starting point.<br />
<br />
-- Glenn Fleishman (glennf.com)</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table><br><br>
</div><ul><li><font class="pn-normal"><a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=NS-Comments&amp;file=index&amp;req=showreply&amp;tid=82&amp;sid=35&amp;pid=77&amp;mode=&amp;order=&amp;thold=#82">Re: Waffling</a></font><font class="pn-sub"> by pbx on Nov 13, 2002 - 02:26 PM</font><br><ul><li><font class="pn-normal"><a class="pn-normal" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=NS-Comments&amp;file=index&amp;req=showreply&amp;tid=87&amp;sid=35&amp;pid=82&amp;mode=&amp;order=&amp;thold=#87">Re: Waffling</a></font><font class="pn-sub"> by gareth on Nov 13, 2002 - 10:27 PM</font><br></ul></ul></div></td>
